<li id="cite_note-36"><b><a href="#cite_ref-36" title="">^</a></b> Normal 0 false false false MicrosoftInternetExplorer4 “I, myself, have often spoken of the “two lungs” – the East and the West – without which Europe could not breathe. There will be no peaceful Europe in the future, nor one whose civilisation will shine forth, without this osmosis and this sharing of values which are different yet complementary. It is on this “humus” that the Europeans are called to build up their common house” (John Paul II 22 December 1989)</li>
